# img-src is intentionally broad ('self' https: data:) — the Simpli.fi ad pixel
# (Dani Tubio's campaigns) fans out cookie-sync image pixels to ~25 rotating ad
# exchanges; a named allowlist breaks retargeting whenever the partner list changes.
# Scripts and connect-src remain strictly allowlisted.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Robots-Tag: index, follow
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  # Single site-wide CSP. The embedded Sanity Studio (/studio) lives on this same
  # origin, and CF Pages enforces multiple CSP headers as an AND (most restrictive
  # wins) — so a path-scoped looser policy for /studio does NOT work. Instead this
  # one policy keeps the marketing site on a named allowlist while also permitting
